com.mojang.datafixers.optics.profunctors

Interface ReCocartesian<P extends K2,Mu extends ReCocartesian _>

  • Type Parameters:
    P - The transformation type.
    Mu - The witness type of this profunctor.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Mu<P>, Kind2 P, Profunctor P
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Forget.Instance

    public interface ReCocartesian<P extends K2,Mu extends ReCocartesian _>
extends Profunctor P
    A profunctor that supports converting a transformation on one of the types in an Either into a transformation on that type. This type class implements the inverse of Cocartesian.
    Type Shape:
    %.Type. %0
    API Note:
    The name ReCocartesian is short for "reified cocartesian", though one could also think of it as a "reverse" or "inverse" operation.
    See Also:
    Cocartesian

    • Method Detail

      • unleft

        <A,B,C> P<A,B> unleft(P<(A|C),(B|C)> input)
        Converts a transformation on the left type in an Either into a transformation on that type, discarding the invariant right type. This method is the inverse of Cocartesian.left(App2).
        Type Parameters:
        A - The input transformed type.
        B - The output transformed type.
        C - The invariant right type in the Either.
        Parameters:
        input - The Either transformation.
        Returns:
        A transformation that operates on the left type of the Either.

      • unright

        <A,B,C> P<A,B> unright(P<(C|A),(C|B)> input)
        Converts a transformation on the right type in an Either into a transformation on that type, discarding the invariant left type. This method is the inverse of Cocartesian.right(App2).
        Type Parameters:
        A - The input transformed type.
        B - The output transformed type.
        C - The invariant left type in the Either.
        Parameters:
        input - The Either transformation.
        Returns:
        A transformation that operates on the right type of the Either.
